</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unasren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nasren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/16/01 8:47:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Cleric BP effect</span><hr size=1> I hate to be negative but a 9 second cast time that prevents you from casting another spell and can and does get resisted often is not a great trade off.<br>
<br>
Celestial elixer is a lvl59 spell that costs 300mana to cast.<br>
<br>
MoK is a lvl56 spell that costs 125 mana to cast and takes 3 seconds to cast.<br>
<br>
So in the 9 seconds I could have casted MoK almost 3 times and only sepnt 375 mana not that bad.<br>
<br>
A better effect that could have prevented downtime and been close to the mana usage and usefulness of celestial elixer would be Bulwark of Faith a lvl57 350mana AC buff. This would not have been unbalancing as it does not do any healing and would have improved a major mana sink. That of ac buffing.<br>
<br>
If they really wanted to win back Clerics belief that Verant does not hate us completely they could have added Naltrons mark or Aegolism.<br>
<br>
Instead they put a low mana, high resist Mark of Uselessness effect on the BP's. I know that they did adjust the healing factor of MoK but it at 3 to 5 points healed per hit with the strength of the mobs hitting back for MoK is still no longer a good spell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 1172<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/16/01 11:11:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Cleric BP effect</span><hr size=1> Damn, I'd love to see our ac buffs on items, that'd make it so that it'd be worth doing on casters as well as just the tanks. <p><CENTER>Hethral Kegslayer<BR>
